cs.DC, cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.LG

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the MapReduce framework, which is a widely used parallel computing platform for processing big data on tera- and peta-byte scale. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also likely as the paper investigates the computational power of MapReduce algorithms compared to combinational Boolean circuits commonly used for parallel computations. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is another possible category as the paper develops an intricate simulation technique to show that any problem in NC can be solved by a MapReduce computation in O(T(n)/ log n) rounds. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with the complexity of algorithms and their efficiency in processing big data. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the practical relevance of the results for solving problems in NC^1, which includes many practically relevant problems.
